thread.title_full: Pa. football: King leads Judge past Roman

title: Pa. football: King leads Judge past Roman
text:
More coverage: Southeastern Pa. high school sports Father Judge heads to Plymouth Whitemarsh to take on eighth-ranked division rival St. Joseph's Prep on Saturday at 7 p.m.
Catholic League AAA. Jaye McNeil ran 23 times for 156 yards and three touchdowns to power Archbishop Ryan in a 42-6 win over Archbishop Carroll at Northeast. Matt Romano completed 10 of 15 passes for 157 yards, including a 55-yarder to Cha Cha Gary for a second-quarter touchdown. The junior quarterback started the scoring with a 25-yard touchdown run. Jeremy Smith caught five passes for 70 yards. A.J. McAleer made 12 tackles. 
Public AAAA. Peter Hutton had 10 carries for 232 yards and four touchdowns to lead West Philadelphia over Mastery North, 44-20, at the Northwest Super Site. Khalil Nelson rushed 11 times for 149 yards and three TDs for Mastery North. 
Suburban One Continental. Brandon McIlwain ran for four touchdowns to carry host Council Rock North over Truman, 34-15. 
Pioneer Athletic Conference. Phoenixville scored 10 second-half points, and the visiting Phantoms held off host Pope John Paul II, 10-7. Biron Miguel Garcia Ramirez hit a 42-yard field goal in the third quarter, and Matt Garcia tacked on a 24-yard touchdown in the fourth. He ran 19 times for 140 yards. 
Brandon Tinson's third-quarter touchdown run, his second, broke a 7-7 tie, and host Pottstown went on to beat Upper Perkiomen, 21-3. 
Bicentennial. New Hope-Solebury scored 40 of its points before halftime in a 55-8 romp at Lower Moreland. In the half, Nick Garritano connected with Blake Hildebrandt on a pair of touchdown passes and Brendan Shadle rushed for two touchdowns. 
Delco Christian's offense racked up more than 400 rushing yards in a 34-7 rout of visiting Calvary Christian. 
Nonleague. Basil Wilson ran for four touchdowns, including two of 35 yards or more, to pace Strawberry Mansion in a 46-32 win over Immaculate Conception at 29th and Chalmers Park. The junior also completed a 26-yard pass to Murell Kearney for a touchdown. Isaiah Johnson and Yassir Cooley each had an interception. 
David Williams had five carries for 62 yards and a touchdown in Boys' Latin's 52-0 rout of visiting People's Prep Charter (N.J.). Troy Hester connected with Deandre Salters for a 35-yard touchdown pass. The Warriors quarterback also ran 20 yards for a touchdown. Malik Johnson rushed four times for 64 yards. Devin Jones, Damien Sears, and Todd Gregory each had an interception.
